					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-632331#post-1729276</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-632331/scp-1603#post-1729276</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 12 Mar 2013 07:31:37 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>RhettSarlin</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>300030</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Actually I disagree with the 767 vibe thing. They have vastly different effects. One's a monster using pictures to suck you into it, this just plain hijacks your memories. If I was going to assign any kind of &quot;vibe&quot; to this, it'd be 426, with the subversion of your sense of self, in this case subverting your own memories if your personal history and changing your self image to that of a person responsible for a murder. Yet still different enough that I see absolutely no reason to go &quot;eh&quot; at it just because someone else wrote something it reminds you of. Upvoted with great abandon, and supporting TroyL's initial awestruck reaction.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
