					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I found this quite intriguing and have upvoted. A couple of things I found puzzling:<br /> - Does the affected individual gain supernatural knowledge of the means of the murder or not? The reference to 'vivid and specific memories' suggests so, but later mention that they will adapt their story when told new information and the interview where they correct themselves suggests not.<br /> - The footnote for 'Fred' says he was mentioned before; unless this is just a reference to where it says places and people are confabulated by the subject.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
